officemax inc the office supplies retailer being acquired by boise cascade has selected the chicago office of ddb worldwide part of the omnicom group to handle its account the chicago office of j walter thompson had handled the account since may billings were estimated at 40 million ralph poore a spokesman at boise cascade amy hoffar a spokeswoman at ddb and owen dougherty a spokesman at thompson declined to comment on reports of the decision in adagecom and adweekcom but executives involved said the decision came after a review that began this month other agencies were included officemax had shifted its account to thompson part of the wpp group from offices of publicis worldwide part of the publicis groupe to continue working with barry krause who resigned from publicis in february to join thompson the acquisition of officemax by boise cascade announced two months later is expected to close by the end of the year

